"Henri J. Schlereth" <henris@bga.com> writes:
> Would any of you kind beings care to point me in the right directions
> on what I would need to do to compile the kernel using kgcc. The
> Makefile has HOSTCC=gcc and I thought I would have to change that to
> = kgcc. If I am right is that the only place I need to change things?
This should probably be asked on the Redhat pinstripe list, as that is
(afaik) the only distribution using a "kgcc".  
As for how to do it, install the kernel source rpm and take a look at
the diffs and spec file.
